children.subject:
When considering how doable it would be, I think considering what will be webcasted is key: 170 is usually webcasted, whereas 120 is never webcasted.

So if you felt okay in 61b/70 about algorithms, you can probably get away with being in-absentia for 170.  If not... then this may not work out well.  (imo, I would prioritize 120 in fall.  As mentioned before, the higher level signal processing/control classes are offered only in the spring.  I wouldn't say 120 isn't useful without 123 however, since it teaches/explores a "new world" that will show up in many classes (for example the FFT/DFT); another great class besides 123 is C128, control theory.)

OP here: I was planning on overriding (through SIS) so as to take both classes simultaneously especially because I really want to take 120 in the fall. Does anyone know how viable this is especially considering factors such as overlapping finals? Has anyone had a similar experience?

I was looking into this and unfortunately you can't because they decided to schedule 120 and 170 at the same time this year despite being the two classes being a popular combo.

I don't know how easy it would be to take classes that overlap in time.
Hit me up if you do this combination or a similar one. Strongly considering taking EE 120, 61C and 168 next semester
